I"š<p><a href="https://oru.com">Orange and Rockland Utility</a> is an energy provider in NY and NJ, USA.
The <code>oru</code> sensor platform fetches your current energy usage from your ORU smart meter.</p>
<h2>Configuration</h2>
<p>To add the <code>oru</code> sensor to your installation, add your <code>meter_number</code> to your <code>configuration.yaml</code> file:</p>
<pre><code class="language-yaml"># Example configuration.yaml entry
sensor:
  - platform: oru
    meter_number: YOUR_METER_NUMBER
</code></pre>
<div class="config-vars">
  <h3><a class="title-link" name="configuration-variables" href="#configuration-variables"></a> Configuration Variables</h3>
  <dl class=''><dt><a class='title-link' name='meter_number' href='#meter_number'></a> meter_number</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='string'>string</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Required)</span><span class='description'><p>The meter number of your smart meter with Orange and Rockland Utility.</p>
</span></p></dd></dl>
</div>
<p><code>meter_number</code> is the smart meter number. It can be found on your energy bill, on the top left corner, alongside your account number.</p>
